#### Allele frequency checked before with:

plink --bfile /path/to/files --freq --out /path/to/freq

### **PLINK Merge from VCF Files **
#### **Step 1: Convert per-chromosome VCFs to PLINK binary format**
###For each chromosome VCF file (`chr<chr>.dose.vcf.gz`), convert it to PLINK binary format (`.bed`, `.bim`, `.fam`) using **PLINK v2**.
###Apply filters:
##* **Minor Allele Count (MAC) â‰¥ 5**


# Loop through chromosomes 1 to X (i.e. 1 to 23)
for chr in {1..22} X; do
    plink2 \
        --vcf chr${chr}.empiricalDose.vcf.gz \
        --make-bed \
        --mac 5 \
        --out ${array_name}_chr${chr}_rsq3
done



#### **Step 2: Create a merge list for chromosomes 2 to X**
###Prepare a plain text file `merge.txt` listing the `.bed`, `.bim`, and `.fam` files for chromosomes 2 to X.


${array_name}_chr2_rsq3.bed ${array_name}_chr2_rsq3.bim ${array_name}_chr2_rsq3.fam
${array_name}_chr3_rsq3.bed ${array_name}_chr3_rsq3.bim ${array_name}_chr3_rsq3.fam
...
${array_name}_chrX_rsq3.bed ${array_name}_chrX_rsq3.bim ${array_name}_chrX_rsq3.fam



#### **Step 3: Merge all chromosomes using PLINK v1.9**
###Use **PLINK v1.9** to merge all chromosomes, starting with chromosome 1 and merging the rest via `--merge-list`.


plink \
    --bfile ${array_name}_chr1_rsq3 \
    --merge-list merge.txt \
    --make-bed \
    --out ${array_name}_chrall_rsq3
